issue.title: Using this project in systems with different disks and different cooling
issue.body:
Hello. First of all, thank you very much for this project.

I plan to use it, but I have a question about the possibility of adding some feature.

I use Supermicro X10SRH-CLN4F in Supermicro CSE-846 case, which in addition to the front drive cages has 2 more places for 2.5 drives, in my case these are two hot server class NVME SSDs, which heat up much more than HDDs, and are also located in such a way that their cooling by the standard cooling system is very poor. The script selects the speed based on the highest temperature, but due to the strong difference in the types of drives and their location, this information is not entirely reliable. It is more important for me to save the front HDDs from the heat.

Therefore, I would like to suggest a feature to somehow be in such situations. For example, use the average temperature of all drives. Or exclude some drives from the check. The same logic can be added for CPUs in a multi-socket motherboard.

issue.title: Polkadot Kurtosis Package fails to run sometimes

labels.name: cli
labels.description: For bugs relating to the CLI

issue.body:
### What's your CLI version?

0.86.15

### Description & steps to reproduce

`kurtosis run github.com/hugobyte/polkadot-kurtosis-package`
```
Error in cloning git repository 'https://github.com/hugobyte/polkadot-kurtosis-package.git' to '/kurtosis-data/tmp-repositories/tmp-repo-dir-484379524/hugobyte/polkadot-kurtosis-package'. Make sure that 'https://github.com/hugobyte/polkadot-kurtosis-package.git' exists and is a public repository.
```

This should not happen as [the package](https://github.com/HugoByte/polkadot-kurtosis-package/tree/main) is public. On a subsequent `kurtosis run .` the package is able to load, thus the behavior is non determinstic.

### Desired behavior

The package always runs because it is public

### What is the severity of this bug?

Papercut; this bug is frustrating, but I have a workaround.

### What area of the product does this pertain to?

CLI: the Command Line Interface

comment.body:
> Hey [@solcates](https://github.com/solcates) - my suggestion right now would be to manually `git clone https://github.com/ethpandaops/ethereum-package.git` onto your system and run `kurtosis run .` from the the base directory of the ethereum packge repo. If you need the ethereum package to be imported within another package you can use a combination of cloning the repo locally + a [replace directive](https://docs.kurtosis.com/advanced-concepts/kurtosis-yml/#replace) to accomplish the same thing. LMK if this works for you as a workaround

works, but painful. `cat cat ethereum-package/kurtosis.yml`
```yaml
name: "github.com/ethpandaops/ethereum-package"

replace:
    github.com/kurtosis-tech/redis-package: ../redis-package
    github.com/kurtosis-tech/postgres-package: ../postgres-package
    github.com/kurtosis-tech/mongodb-package: ../mongodb-package
    github.com/kurtosis-tech/prometheus-package: ../prometheus-package
    github.com/bharath-123/db-adminer-package: ../db-adminer-packag
```
`kurtosis run ./ethereum-package --args-file  xxx/network_params.yaml --image-download missing`

commits.message: Build component for web via jco

Complete switch to component model

This is a little weird and there's a bunch of extra stuff carried along,
so bear with me a bit.

1.      We declare the interface we want in
        `wasm-component/wit/world.wit`, and implement it in
        `wasm-component/src/lib.rs`.
2.      In `wasm-component/nice-dice.wasm.do`, we generate the binding
        code with `cargo component bindings`, then build the WASM
        component with `cargo component build --release`.

        This component can be embedded in other component-model
        contexts; however, we're going to distribute it for the web,
        which doesn't have native component support. So...

3.      In `wasm-component/pkg.dir.do`, we use `jco` to transpile the
        WASM component into an ESM module, i.e. to create the JS-to-WASM
        bindings based on the component's own interface definition.
        Note that we don't `--minify` at this stage, because we're going
        to bundle it with minification in the next step.

        This generates several files in `wasm-component/pkg/`.

4.      In `wasm-component/nice-dice.js.do`, we invoke `esbuild` to
        bundle the JS portions together, since `jco` uses some glue via
        its own imports. (The WASM files are still separate.)

        This generates `nice-dice.js` and `nice-dice.js.map`.

5.      Finally, in `dist.dir.do`, we collect all of the artifacts
        together into the `dist/` directory, including the demo page and
        glue code.
Additional WASM component optimizations and fixes
Fix usage of component; initialize properly

issue.title: Corrupted video files and vide engines **SOLVED**. Fix can be part of SE tools.
issue.body:
I had a lot of problems with some video files; SE video engines showed scrambled/frozen video now and then, while the players reproduced them without any problem. You can try to use different codecs, the newest FFMPEG, but these files will stay broken. What is the reason? 

They have VFR, variable frame rate, or wrong timestamps. Broken indexes. Missing keyframes. How to solve this? We all have FFMPEG in our SE. Steps:
1. Put the ffmpeg.exe in the PATH environment variable. You can use the path from the SE, or you can (better) make a new path, for instance: C:/FFMPEG/ffmpeg.exe. Some new path that is not dependent of the place where SE is installed or unpacked. 
 
2. Use the command:

ffmpeg -i corrupted_file_name.mp4 -vf fps=30 -c:v libx264 -preset veryfast -crf 23 -c:a aac corrupted_file_name_fixed.mp4

-vf fps=30          Converts Variable Frame Rate ‚Üí Constant
libx264               Re-encodes to industry-standard H.264
-crf 23                Keeps good quality at smaller size
-c:a aac              Re-encodes audio to compatible AAC format

The new video is frame-perfect, seekable, timestamp-stable, and works with any video engine, including mpv, DirectShow.

You can put it in the BAT program to make your life easier. This line in the command prompt will fix the file; you need a minute for the 23-minute TV Show, and it will work without any frozen/scrambled parts, and with DirectShow and mpv video engine without any problem. 

It is nice to have this, because you will always encounter some corrupted file, that player will reproduce OK, but in SE it will be a disaster if we talk about the video engine. 

I SUGGEST that this become part of the SUBTITLE EDIT, something like Tools/Fix variable frame rate. The program should make a PATH to accept our corrupted file and start the routine that will with ffmpeg to solve the whole problem.

comment.body:
Good job Nikolaj. I can see that you didn't use -crf parameter that is supposed to keep the file smaller, but the size of the output file is THE SAME as I get with my batch programs. So, its output size is SMALLER and it is more than great. The output file mkv and mp4 are normal, no scrambling/freezing/darkness.

To be sure if something goes wrong with the parameters, do we always need to right-click on the GENERATE button to reach the parameters for FFMPEG, or is it stored maybe in settings.xml, or some other place we can reach? Not to be forced to change parameters every time we use this conversion if we want constantly to use some other parameters. I always use portable versions, that is, I use your beta versions. 

It is just in case of emergency, or some bug, I am more than satisfied with this version or your program. And I am happy that I don't need to enter subtitles, the video, and then I get the two dialog windows (choose a file, generate) you fixed this, I just loaded the video file and I got the generate dialogue immediately after this step.
